SELECT 'Episode 2: Among the Chosen, and the Meaning of His Name', 'kisah-dzulkifli-02-termasuk-al-akhyar', 'en', 'kisah-dzulkifli', 2, 1, 'The second time the Qur''an mentions Dzulkifli is in Surah Sad, again beside prophets and named among the chosen. Allah said, "And remember Isma''il, Al-Yasa'' (Elisha), and Dhul-Kifl — and all are among the outstanding" (Qur''an 38:48).

The word "al-akhyar" means the chosen and the best. So the Qur''an gives Dhul-Kifl three combined praises from two places: he is patient (21:85), he is righteous (21:86), and he is among the best/chosen (38:48).

As for the name "Dhul-Kifl," the commentators explain its linguistic sense. "Al-Kifl" can mean a share or portion (a multiplied share of reward), and can also mean a responsibility or guarantee (kafalah). Some scholars read it as: he was named so because he took on and guaranteed a trust, then fulfilled it faithfully. In honesty: the Qur''an itself does not explain the reason for the name, so the above is a linguistic interpretation, not a definitive certainty.

Reflection: the title "the chosen" is not given for nothing. It is the fruit of long patience and obedience. A good name, too, often carries a meaning of example — in Dhul-Kifl''s case, the meaning of faithfully discharging a responsibility.

Source & Note: the core evidence is from the Qur''an, 38:48 and 21:85-86. The explanation of "al-kifl" follows the well-known linguistic notes in the tafsir works (e.g. Ibn Kathir, al-Tabari); since the Qur''an does not detail it, this is offered as interpretation, not certainty.', 0, 'qc_pending', 'ai_original', 'published', 1.0,
  (SELECT id FROM ayah WHERE surah_id = 38 AND number = 48), NULL, datetime('now');

